                <h1>Significance of the Petition of Right Explained</h1>
                <p>The Petition of Right, established in 1628, was a pivotal document in the struggle for civil liberties in England. It challenged the authority of King Charles I by asserting that everyone, including the monarch, was subject to the law. This set the precedent for parliamentary sovereignty and the protection of individual rights against arbitrary rule.</p>
